<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1910/520143-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.The launch will be on Sunday, 6 October and will end on Wednesday, 6 November 2019. Africa Magic Nollywood Stars will offer all active DStv and GOtv Max and Plus subscribers the occasion to watch drama, comedy, suspense, intrigue from the biggest Nollywood titles, 24 hours and seven days a week with no repeats. The channels director of Africa Magic, Wangi Mba-Uzoukwu stated, “Africa Magic is undoubtedly the home for first-class movies and series from Nollywood. We have curated the biggest Nollywood movies – both new and epic – that have featured on our channels and will air them for one month with no repeats.”The stars who will be on DStv and GOtv screens on this pop-up channel are Omotola Jalade-Ekeinde, Rita Dominic, Majid Michel, Deyemi Okanlawon, Blossom Chukwujekwu and many more. The pop-up channel will offer viewers with huge titles such as The Big Fat Lie, Getting Over Him, 72 Hours,  Brother Jekwu, Remember Me and What Lies Within. Also on the line-up will be the big wins from the 2018 Africa Magic Viewers’ Choice Awards; Isoken for Best Movie West Africa, Best Supporting Actress Drama (Lydia Forson), Best Director in a Movie, Alter Ego for Best Writer, Best Actress (Omotola Jalade-Ekeinde) and Lotana for Best Art Director.